@edition "2026.6"

-- D1(ii) frontier guardrail. This program is VALID (it type-checks clean — a `_test`,
-- not a `_bad`), but it destructures a CONSTRUCTOR in its `match` arms (`Ok(v)` /
-- `Error(e)`), which binds the payload of a heap value the compute spine has no
-- representation for yet. The differential harness must report it `unsupported` — a
-- CLEAN refusal at the compiler frontier — never a miscompile, never a JS crash.
--
-- This is the backend-slice analogue of a `_bad` twin: a backend slice adds no
-- checker rejection rule, so the guarantee under test is "the compiler refuses what
-- it cannot yet lower, loudly", asserted by the harness rather than by an error
-- count. D1(ii) moved the frontier PAST scalar `match` (literal/binder/guard arms now
-- compile — see compile_match_test); the frontier now sits at heap-value
-- destructuring. Constructor/tuple/record patterns lower in D1(iii); when they do,
-- this file flips from `unsupported` to a MATCH with no edit.

def unwrap(r: Result Number String): Number
  match r
    | Ok(v) -> v
    | Error(e) -> 0

def main(): Effect [io] ()
  println(unwrap(Ok(42)))
  println(unwrap(Error("nope")))
